+## Future: Crowdsourced Tradecraft from User Data
+
+### The Idea
+
+Use anonymized quote data from real users to generate and improve tradecraft documents. Instead of guessing what materials contractors need, learn from what they actually use.
+
+### What Data Could Be Analyzed
+
+- **Project names** → Common job types ("panel upgrade", "200a panel", "service upgrade" cluster together)
+- **Materials added** → What contractors actually use for each job type
+- **Quantities** → Real-world amounts (not textbook estimates)
+- **Labor hours** → Actual time estimates from the field
+
+### How It Could Work
+
+1. **Opt-in data sharing** - Users consent to share anonymized quote patterns
+2. **Cluster similar projects** - Group freeform project names into job types
+3. **Find material patterns** - "For panel upgrades, 80% of contractors add X, Y, Z"
+4. **Generate/validate tradecraft** - Create docs from real data, not AI guesses
+5. **Feedback loop** - "Was this material list helpful?" improves suggestions
+
+### Implementation Considerations
+
+| Consideration | Approach |
+|---------------|----------|
+| **Privacy** | Explicit opt-in: "Help improve Drew by sharing anonymized quote data" |
+| **Data quality** | Normalize freeform project names via clustering/NLP |
+| **Volume** | Need critical mass of Premium users before patterns emerge |
+| **Validation** | Cross-reference with expert review (Wyatt) |
+
+### The Flywheel
+
+```
+More users → More quote data → Better tradecraft → Better Drew → More users
+```
+
+This creates a defensible moat. Tradecraft based on real contractor behavior is more valuable than AI-generated guesses.
+
+### When to Pursue
+
+- After Premium user base reaches ~100+ active users
+- When quote volume is sufficient for pattern detection
+- As a v2/v3 enhancement, not launch priority
